      "raw_text": "r. A. Ballinger, the Seattle at\ntorney President Roosevelt select\ned to take charge of the general\nUnited States land office in the\nmidst Of red hot campaign against\nland thieves, arrived in Spokane\nthis morning from Boise. He Is &C.\ncompanied by his private secretary\nand is making roundup of land\nOffices on his way home from Wash.\nington.\n\n\nThe commissioner spent most of\nthe day at the Spokane hotel rest.\ning. He has been travelling steadily\nfor the past 2 weeks. Tomorrow\nhe will look into the local United\nStates land Office and straighten\nwhat kinks he finds. His chief mis-\nsion on this trip is to abolish as\nmuch red tape as possible."
    }
